       <h3>The Benefits of Belonging</h3> 
       <p>UC&nbsp;Riverside offers a comprehensive and competitive array of benefit choices. Employment benefits are an important part of your compensation package. Below is an overview of the benefits the University provides, depending on your type of appointment.</p> 
       <ul class="texttab-control"> 
        <li><a href="#news">What's New</a></li> 
        <li><a href="#health">Health &amp; Welfare Plans</a></li> 
        <li><a href="#retirement">Retirement &amp; Savings Plans</a></li> 
       </ul> 
       <div id="news"> 
        <div class="texttab-column"> 
         <h4><strong>Bright Horizons Care Advantage - New Resource</strong></h4> 
         <p>Bright Horizon Care Advantage is now offering an instructional presentation to get information and details about how to participate in <strong>Years Ahead</strong>.</p> 
         <ul> 
          <li><strong>Years Ahead</strong> provides access to senior care providers, including Certified Senior Care Advisers who can offer consultative Senior Care solutions. To view the Brainshark presentation, please <a href="https://www.brainshark.com/brighthorizons/vu?pi=zHIzCvE8az2weVz0">click here</a>.</li> 
         </ul> 
         <p>In addition to <strong>Years Ahead</strong>, Bright Horizons Care Advantage also offers <strong>Sittercity</strong>, providing access to a wide range of childcare providers including nannies, baby sitters and even care for your pets.</p> 
         <p>For more information about the Bright Horizons Care Advantage benefit, visit UCR Human Resources &gt; <a href="/worklife/personal_balance.html">Personal Balance</a>.</p> 
         <h4 class="section3"><strong>2015 New Employee Benefits Orientation<br></strong></h4> 
         <p><span style="color: windowtext;">We are pleased to announce the 2015 dates for New Employee Benefits Orientation. If you have a colleague or team member who has yet to attend, this is a great opportunity for them to come and learn about their UC benefits.<br></span></p> 
         <p><span style="color: windowtext;">The first 2015 New Employee Benefits Orientation will occur on Thursday, February 5th from 8:00 a.m. - 12:00 p.m.&nbsp; Please join us at the EDC (Employee Development Center) located at Human Resources, 1160 University Avenue adjacent to the UCR Extension Center.</span></p> 
         <p><span style="color: windowtext;">To see a list of upcoming dates, please <a href="/2015newemployeeorientation.pdf">click here</a>.</span></p> 
         <p><span style="color: windowtext;">Please send any questions to: <a href="mailto:benefits@ucr.edu" target="_blank">benefits@ucr.edu</a></span></p> 
         <ul> 
          <ul class="more_links"> 
           <li><a href="http://ucnet.universityofcalifornia.edu/news/employment.html" target="_blank">More News</a></li> 
          </ul> 
         </ul> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
